<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFA5FF8FFCFBFBDC83DDFB2D" blockId="27.[813,1421,979,1285]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Therophytes, native with distribution in the Southern Cone Region of South America.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFA5FF8FFCFBFB1382D2FA89" blockId="27.[813,1421,979,1285]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFA5FF8FFCFBFB138359FB4C" bold="true" box="[850,1031,1193,1217]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Characteristics.</emphasis>
Annual herb with tetragonal, pubescent stems. Leaves pubescent, ovate, with apex acute. Pseudoverticils formed by 2 leaves and 2 foliar stipules.
</paragraph>
