<subSubSection id="C31990A8FFA2FF88FF67FDF9862AFC8E" pageId="28" pageNumber="1031" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFA2FF88FF67FDF9862AFC8E" blockId="28.[168,776,479,771]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1031">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFA2FF88FF67FDF9860EFDD6" bold="true" box="[206,336,579,603]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1031">Comments.</emphasis>
This is a frequent species in the study area. It grows in shaded, moist soils and under the trees. It grows with other 
<taxonomicName id="4C03B8A0FFA2FF88FEDCFD3C8546FD13" box="[373,536,646,670]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Galium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="28" pageNumber="1031" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFA2FF88FEDCFD3C869BFD13" box="[373,453,646,670]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1031">Galium</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
such as 
<taxonomicName id="4C03B8A0FFA2FF88FDC6FD3D85BCFD13" box="[623,738,647,670]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Galium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="28" pageNumber="1031" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aparine">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFA2FF88FDC6FD3D85BCFD13" box="[623,738,647,670]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1031">G. aparine</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an annual herb with sticky hairs on leaves and fruits, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C03B8A0FFA2FF88FD44FD12866EFD6C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Galium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="28" pageNumber="1031" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hipocarpium">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFA2FF88FD44FD12866EFD6C" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1031">G. hipocarpium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a perennial herb with long peduncle flow- ers and red berries.
</paragraph>
